Document

public Document(java.lang.Long id,
                java.lang.String contentId,
                java.lang.String account,
                java.lang.Long essRequestId,
                java.lang.String author,
                java.util.Date docCreatedDate,
                java.lang.String originalFile,
                java.lang.String format,
                java.lang.Long fileSize,
                java.lang.String title,
                java.util.Date docLastModifiedDate,
                java.lang.String errorMessage)

Create a new Document instance with the values passed in.

Note that creating a new instance of this object does not upload the document to the Content Repository.

Parameters:
id - uniquely identifies a document in the Content Repository.
contentId - identifies a document in the Content Repository but not the specific version of the document. A document may have many versions as it changes over time.
account - category used to distinguish different groups of documents.
essRequestId - uniquely identifies an ESS (Enterprise Scheduling System) job.
author - user who uploaded the document.
docCreatedDate - the date the document was uploaded.
originalFile - the original name of the document.
format - the type of the content. For example, plain/text.
fileSize - size of the document.
title - document name.
docLastModifiedDate - the date when the document was modified. This will be the same as the docCreatedDate if the file has not been modified.
errorMessage - only populated if there is an issue interacting with the Content Repository. Provides information as to the nature of the problem being encountered.

delete

Deletes this document from the Content Repository.

update

public void update()
Updates this document in the Content Repository with the process id. The process id is another name for essRequestId. In future, this method may update based on all the fields in the document not just the essRequestId.
